{
  "texts": [
    "After all the independent blocks are aligned, they should be stitched together into a single globally aligned stack.",
    "We define the stitch field between block N and block N + 1 as that obtained by aligning the overlapping section region of block N + 1 to the same sections in block N and performing vector voting operations across the obtained fields (Fig. 3b).",
    "The stitch fields can be used to create a global alignment as follows.",
    "For each block, the stitch fields from the preceding blocks are composed to create an accumulated transformation that is applied to all sections in the block (Fig. 3).",
    "This straightforward procedure can result in good alignment, in the sense that neurites follow smooth paths through the stack."
  ]
}